  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to report suspicious transactions or activities to the appropriate authorities. However, the specific details can vary by jurisdiction. In general, these requirements often include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n2. Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n3. Customer due diligence\n4. Record-keeping requirements\n\nI want to be clear that I can provide general information about this topic, but I cannot give specific legal advice. If you have detailed questions about money laundering reporting requirements, I recommend consulting a legal professional.",
